    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5x^{2}r^{2}+7xr+2}{-9xr-5-4x^{2}r^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{5xr+2}{4xr+5}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5x^{2}r^{2}+7xr+2}{-9xr-5-4x^{2}r^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{\left(5xr+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(xr+1\right)}}{{-4x^{2}r^{2}-9xr-5}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(5xr+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(xr+1\right)}}{{-\left(4x^{2}r^{2}+9xr+5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(5xr+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(xr+1\right)}}{{-\left(4xr+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(xr+1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{5xr+2}{4xr+5}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
